Erotic and Rock

EROTIC AND ROCK

Don't the erotic and rock go together ? isnt rock music all about sex ?

yet watching so many rock concerts, the erotic rarely gets a look in !

Live aid is a case in point, why was I so bored to death by the big event ?

how much of rocking all over the world can you take ?

The stage forever full of beefy guys in jeans playing guitars... yawn...

it needs some foxy babes...

A dance group like Hot gossip would fit the bill...

Rock and pop needs a bit of theatre.

go here

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B2Tkx6BgRFE

No. Rock music is about rock music, sex is about sex.

I would argue that Mick and Keiths love of blues music in the early 60s.... was the raw sex that was often in the music and lyrics...

" Im a king bee

Buzzin around your hive

I can make lots of honey,

Let me come inside....

It was a while before I realized the full sexual connotations of that

song and many more.

Those early black writers and musicians were nt messing around, they were writing and singing overtly about sex ... putting sex in the lyrics and using rythms and beats that enhanced sex.

Guys like Mick, Keith and John Mayal were picking up on it bigtime and getting the sexual and erotic messages..... and very

soon the 60s were beginning to swing !

Think back to the early 60s it was all Alma Cogan and very twee music.

Mick and the guys discovered a secret underworld of songs and music.. mainly

from the States and they launched all that raw sex on the unsuspecting British public...

much to the shock of Mary Whitehouse !
